The paper presents a system for sketch-based face image editing using a convolutional neural network. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) as the system involves image manipulation and rendering. The use of a neural network for learning to render image regions corresponds to the input strokes suggests machine learning (MM) and artificial intelligence (AI) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the training procedure and network architecture, indicating a focus on machine learning (MM) and deep learning (LG).
